</paragraph>
<paragraph id="201EA5149190A71A9B96271C19208F61" pageId="11" pageNumber="100">
Traditionally, two subspecies have been recognized. 
<taxonomicName id="A1AC9DDF7A065C9E98A28BCBC3858B1B" authority="M.Roser &amp; H.R.Hamashaon Hagen, 2012" authorityName="M.Roser &amp; H.R.Hamashaon Hagen" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Oloptum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oloptum miliaceum subsp. thomasii" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="miliaceum" subSpecies="thomasii">Oloptum miliaceum subsp. thomasii</taxonomicName>
(Duby) Boiss. differs from the typical form in having densely verticillate panicles with 15-30 or more often sterile branches on the lowest whorl (
<bibRefCitation id="0104C6BFC20608E7BDF76DD5B827D886" author="Freitag, H" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="341 - 406" refId="B10" refString="Freitag, H, 1975. The genus Piptatherum (Gramineae) in Southwest Asia. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 33: 341 - 406" title="The genus Piptatherum (Gramineae) in Southwest Asia." volume="33" year="1975">Freitag 1975</bibRefCitation>
). There is genetic variation between these two subspecies in our earlier analyses (
<bibRefCitation id="4B58687E916753AF4D82A63735F23871" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.606015" author="Romaschenko, K" journalOrPublisher="Aarhus University Press, Denmark" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" refId="B25" refString="Romaschenko, K, Peterson, PM, Soreng, RJ, Futorna, O, Susanna, A, 2011. Phylogenetics of Piptatherum s.l. (Poaceae: Stipeae): Evidence for a new genus, Piptatheropsis, and resurrection of Patis. Taxon 60(6): 1703-1716. https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.606015" title="Phylogenetics of Piptatherum s. l. (Poaceae: Stipeae): Evidence for a new genus, Piptatheropsis, and resurrection of Patis. Taxon 60 (6): 1703 - 1716." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.606015" year="2011">Romaschenko et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7192790325E3032D93853429F8B687C4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.611002" author="Romaschenko, K" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="18 - 44" refId="B26" refString="Romaschenko, K, Peterson, PM, Soreng, RJ, Garcia-Jacas, N, Futorna, O, Susanna, A, 2012. Systematics and evolution of the needle grasses (Poaceae: Pooideae: Stipeae) based on analysis of multiple chloroplast loci, ITS, and lemma micromorphology. Taxon 61 (1): 18 - 44, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.611002" title="Systematics and evolution of the needle grasses (Poaceae: Pooideae: Stipeae) based on analysis of multiple chloroplast loci, ITS, and lemma micromorphology." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.611002" volume="61" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
). A molecular study with a larger sample of the subspecies is necessary to fully explore evolutionary relationships.
</paragraph>
